The paper deals with the problem of service chain mapping in a wide area network, which involves the placement of virtual network functions and routing of traffic flows through them. This problem is related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) as it involves optimizing network resource consumption. The paper proposes an integer linear program and a column-generation-based model to solve the problem, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper uses optimization techniques to solve the problem, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
